d3f:BootSector a sh:NodeShape ;
    rdfs:label "Boot Sector" ;
    rdfs:comment "A boot record [boot sector] is the sector of a persistent data storage device (e.g., hard disk, floppy disk, optical disc, etc.) which contains machine code to be loaded into random-access memory (RAM) and then executed by a computer system's built-in firmware (e.g., the BIOS, Das U-Boot, etc.)." ;
