d3f:CentralProcessingUnit a sh:NodeShape ;
    rdfs:label "Central Processing Unit" ;
    rdfs:comment "A central processing unit (CPU), also called a central processor, main processor or just processor, is the electronic circuitry that executes instructions comprising a computer program. The CPU performs basic arithmetic, logic, controlling, and input/output (I/O) operations specified by the instructions in the program. This contrasts with external components such as main memory and I/O circuitry, and specialized processors such as graphics" ;
    sh:closed true ;
