d3f:PhysicalAddress a sh:NodeShape ;
    rdfs:label "Physical Address" ;
    rdfs:comment "In a computer supporting virtual memory, the term physical address is used mostly to differentiate from a virtual address. In particular, in computers utilizing a memory management unit(MMU) to translate memory addresses, the virtual and physical addresses refer to an address before and after translation performed by the MMU, respectively." ;
