d3f:Variability a sh:NodeShape ;
    rdfs:comment "Dispersion (also called variability, scatter, or spread) is the extent to which a distribution is stretched or squeezed. A measure of statistical dispersion is a nonnegative real number that is zero if all the data are the same and increases as the data become more diverse." ;
    sh:closed true ;
    sh:ignoredProperties ( rdf:type ) ;
    sh:targetClass d3f:Variability .

