d3f:WirelessAccessPoint a sh:NodeShape ;
    rdfs:label "Wireless Access Point" ;
    rdfs:comment "In computer networking, a wireless access point (WAP), or more generally just access point (AP), is a networking hardware device that allows other Wi-Fi devices to connect to a wired network. The AP usually connects to a router (via a wired network) as a standalone device, but it can also be an integral component of the router itself. An AP is differentiated from a hotspot which is a physical location where Wi-Fi access is available." ;
